SIMPLE: sorrow
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sorrow
<hw>Sor"row</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>sorwe</ets>,
<ets>sorewe</ets>, <ets>sor<?/e</ets>, AS. <ets>sorg</ets>,
<ets>sorh</ets>; akin to D. <ets>zorg</ets> care, anxiety, OS.
<ets>sorga</ets>, OHG. <ets>sorga</ets>, <ets>soraga</ets>,
<ets>suorga</ets>, G. <ets>sorge</ets>, Icel., Sw., & Dan.
<ets>sorg</ets>, Goth. <ets>sa⟦uacute⟧rga</ets>; of unknown
origin.]</ety> <def>The uneasiness or pain of mind which is produced by
the loss of any good, real or supposed, or by disappointment in the
expectation of good; grief at having suffered or occasioned evil;
regret; unhappiness; sadness.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How great a <qex>sorrow</qex> suffereth now Arcite!</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The safe and general antidote against <qex>sorrow</qex> is
employment.</q> <rj><qau>Rambler.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Grief; unhappiness; regret; sadness; heaviness;
mourning; affliction. See <er>Affliction</er>, and
<er>Grief</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sorrow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sorrow
<hw>Sor"row</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Sorrowed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Sorrowing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>sorowen</ets>,
<ets>sorwen</ets>, <ets>sorhen</ets>, AS. <ets>sorgian</ets>; akin to
Goth. <ets>sa⟦uacute⟧rgan</ets>. See <er>Sorrow</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>To feel pain of mind in consequence of evil
experienced, feared, or done; to grieve; to be sad; to be
sorry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sorrowing</qex> most of all . . . that they should see his
face no more.</q> <rj><qau>Acts xx. 38.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I desire no man to <qex>sorrow</qex> for me.</q> <rj><qau>Sir J.
Hayward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sorrowed</ent>⟦br⟧
